7 #mana-confessional (edited)
Mana
Dear Confessional, This is about to be a long one, but bear with me, okay? I promise its worth it. I feel like I owe you all an apology. I started this game so so so excited and so happy and I feel like the last 2 weeks I have only come in here to cry and be stressed about this game. To be very clear, I am still so excited about this game. I just think that I had one of those 'first-time-ORG-reality-check' type of moments as I started to progress so much further than I ever thought I would in the game. By now, everyone knows that this is my first ORG, but a lot of you may not know that I didn't even know that ORGs existed until a week and a half before I even applied to this season. So talk about being thrown into it, right? Picture a little baby bird in its nest (it's me, I'm the baby bird) and then its mama just kicking out out of the nest to fly (Fish. Fish is the mama). But look Ma...I'm actually flying... This may not come as a shock to some of you, but I'm a little bit of a perfectionist when it comes to the standards to which I hold myself. If I try at something, I better be perfect at it all the time or else I am a failure (yes, I know, I know, that's very unhealthy, that's why we go to therapy kids). So when I started not being perfect at things....woof...that was a hard one to learn how to cope with. (As evidence of my few breakdowns both in here and to Production thank you Production ily). I'm still not great at it, but I find myself better at re-centering myself and just....trying again if I don't get something right the first time. So, why do I feel like I need to apologize to you? Because, there's an aspect of me that also wants to be the light in the room when everything looks bad or bleak or dark. The dark can't consume you if you yourself are light, right? Idk -insert some other cheesy motivational poster crap here-. But the thing is, is that I mean it when I'm cheering everyone else on here. I just need to be better about cheering on myself, I suppose. So here's my self-cheer: Even if I don't win immunity, I still have a chance. I can play my best game and try to survive to FTC by using my head and my heart together. I would still have a chance to say my piece and talk to the jury and hell, if I make it, I do have a shot. I just have to make it, first. And I can do it. I have to believe I can. I know it seems like a goodbye letter. It partially is, I guess, because we are rapidly approaching the end of the game and even if I do make it to FTC, I won't have many more opportunities to post in here like this to you guys. But it's also a thank you. Thanks for watching me cheerlead and breakdown and still somehow come out the other side. I mean it when I say I feel like I could feel your support from the other side of spec chat (idk maybe that's just wishful thinking). Anyways, this has become an essay now (thank god for Nitro). So lastly... Be Safe. Be good. I love you. say it back Mana
Source

I really thought I had it for a bit... Everything was playing out exactly how I wanted... and then boom everything fell apart... I'm still absolutely heartbroken and I will be for a while. I just need some time....... This was one of the wildest ORG experiences I've had, but I still had a lot of fun, with a couple exceptions. I got to meet a lot of really fucking cool people and to play with them all was such a privilege. To all the other players, everything in my conf is for entertainment and I meant no ill intent by anything I said. Everything nice on the other hand, I fully mean and I'm so happy that you were here to make the season special. To the hosts, I think I gave you a lot more crap than you deserved. I merely had high expectations coming into this and when things felt like they came up short of that I felt wrongfully disappointed. I can tell how much effort you all put into this season and I really appreciate you having me on. I really did have a blast and a lot of my expectations were still largely exceeded. I love you all TYSM Finally to the specs, and esecially to my biggest cheerleaders through this all, Cake and Sophia, Sam, Kat, Sunder, Nicole, Brett, Shannon, Allen, Lava, there are way too many of you to even list name by name but I love you all so much. I appreciate anyone who took the time to read any of my conf but to everyone who actively cheered for me, you all inspired me. Lord knows that this was an emotional experience for me but I wouldnt have been able to make it through without you. Thanks for all the kind words, warm wishes, and radical questions. You all mean so much to me Not sure when the next time I play will be. Hopefully Smorgon S22 but idk what my chances are of making it into smorgon anytime soon. I'll see y'all somewhere around the discords soon I'm sure tho GOODBYE FOR NOW, FROM THE SANDWICH QUEEN
